page.title: 05Ecology around Brushford
page.content: Woodland is mostly hardwood,Oak, Ash,Sycamore,Birch.Alder and Willow in wetter ground.Few young Elms due to Dutch Elm disease.Some conifer plant_ ations and Chestnut coppice.Holly and Rowan plentiful.Beech mainly on hedge banks with mixture of Hawthorn,Hazel, Blackthorn Damson,few Crabapple and Christling (Bullace),Wild Rose,Honey_ suckle,Blackberry.Flowers,good variety wetland,Marsh penny wort,Bogbean,Marsh Marigold,Bog pimpernel,orchids,rushes sedges.Woods_bluebell,garlic,wood anemone.Fields_buttercup,daisy,clover, scabious,thistle,celandine,vetch. Banks and hedges_violet,campion,wild strawberry ferns wall pennywort Hops (relic of home brewing) Heather and Whortleberry. Moss and lichen plentiful. Not so common_Double Celandine,Hellborine Twayblade.Plenty Frogs Common Toad and Grass Snake.
